column13: description
DHW scenario member identifier.
Wave scenario member identifier.
Cyclone mortality scenario identifier.
Choice of MCDA approach.
Number of Tabular Acropora to seed per deployment year.
Number of Corymbose Acropora to seed per deployment year.
Number of small massives/encrusting to seed per deployment year.
Assumed reduction in bleaching mortality.
Reduction in DHWs due to shading.
Assisted adaptation in terms of DHW resistance.
Number of years to seed for.
Number of years to shade for.
How many years of projected data to take into account when selecting intervention locations (0 only accounts for current year).
Frequency of seeding site selection (0 is set and forget).
Frequency of shading site selection (0 is set and forget).
Start seeding deployments after this number of years has elapsed.
Start of shading deployments after this number of years has elapsed.
Importance of avoiding wave stress when seeding. Higher values places more weight on areas with low wave stress.
Importance of avoiding heat stress when seeding. Higher values places more weight on areas with low heat stress.
Importance of avoiding wave stress when fogging. Higher values places more weight on areas with low wave stress.
Importance of avoiding heat stress when fogging. Higher values places more weight on areas with low heat stress.
Higher values give preference to locations with high connectivity for shading deployments.
Higher values give preference to locations with high incoming connectivity (i.e., receives larvae from other sites) for enhanced coral deployments.
Higher values give preference to locations with high outgoing connectivity (i.e., provides larvae to other sites) for enhanced coral deployments.
Higher values give preference to depper locations for enhanced coral deployments.
Higher values give greater preference to sites with low coral cover for seeding deployments.
Higher values give preference to sites with high coral cover for shading deployments.
Importance of seeding sites that provide larvae to priority reefs.
Importance of shading sites that provide larvae to priority reefs.
Importance of seeding sites that provide larvae to priority (target) zones.
Importance of shading sites that provide larvae to priority (target) zones.
Tolerance for low proportional space for seeding deployments.
Filters out sites with heat/wave stress above threshold.
Turns distance sorting on or off.
Sites selected by MCDA must be further apart than median(dist)-dist_thresh*median(dist).

Minimum depth for a site to be included for consideration.
Note: This value will be replaced with the shallowest depth value found if all sites are found to be deeper than `depth_min + depth_offset`.
Offset from minimum depth, used to indicate maximum depth.
Heritability of DHW tolerance.
